  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Subjects with a breast abnormality (identified by mammography, ultrasound, MRI and/or a
        clinical examination) summoned for breast biopsy or subjects summoned for a routine
        screening examination.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Gender: female

          -  Age: 18 years and older

          -  Subjects with a breast abnormality (identified by mammography, ultrasound, MRI and/or
             a clinical examination) summoned for breast biopsy or subjects summoned for a routine
             screening examination.

          -  Subject who have signed an informed consent form.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Subjects who have had a mammography, ultrasound, and/or MRI examination performed on
             the day of the study, prior to being &quot;imaged&quot; by RI4.0.

          -  Subjects who have undergone any type of breast surgery throughout the 6 weeks
             preceding the study.

          -  Subjects who have had a breast biopsy performed throughout the 6 weeks preceding the
             study.

          -  Subjects who have undergone a mastectomy.

          -  Subjects who have a large scar (causing breast deformation) following breast
             lumpectomy and/or any other cause (e.g. accident).

          -  Subjects with prior breast reduction surgery or breast augmentation surgery.

          -  Subjects who have a fever on the day of their biopsy.

          -  Subjects who are pregnant.

          -  Subjects who are breast-feeding.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
